independent_work.et:
Täpsed juhised iga ülesande kohta on antud Moodle'is.

1) loenguks ja seminariks ettevalmistamine, sh materjalide lugemine ja lisainfo otsimine;
2) aktiivne osalus loengutes ja seminariaruteludes;
3) õpipäevikud;
4) testid;
5) kirjanduse ülevaate koostamine ühel kursusega seotud teemal.

grade_evaluation.et:
Lõpphinne kujuneb järgmistest hinnatavatest komponentidest:
1) Testid (45%)
The tests are assessed according to:
- Correctness of answers.

2) Õpipäevikute sissekanded (15%)
The reflections in the learning diary are assessed according to:
- Level of critical reflection;
- Clarity and logical consistency.

3) Kirjanduse ülevaade (40%)
The literature review is assessed according to:
-	Clarity and precision of the definition of the focus of the literature review (central issue or research problem and subset of literature);
-	Sufficiency and relevance of the selected of sources; 
-	Level of detail in the review of individual sources and, as a result of a synthesis of the analysis of individual sources, the comprehensiveness of the overview of the literature;
-	Critical assessment of the literature on the basis of the initially introduced criteria and, ultimately, the identification of a gap in the literature in accordance with the presented findings;
-	Logic and coherence of the structure of the review and adherence to language and formatting requirements.
